From: Peng Chao <chao.peng@windriver.com>
Date: Wed, 7 Aug 2013 18:11:17 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 085/134] ACPI / PM: Use string "D3cold" to represent
 ACPI_STATE_D3_COLD

upstream: 898fee4f6ed52b5b5dd159b221d2ad7ce40ae2dd

Make acpi_power_state_string() return "D3cold" as the string
representation of ACPI power state D3cold instead of "D3" returned
currently, which is confusing.

Signed-off-by: Rafael J. Wysocki <rafael.j.wysocki@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Peng Chao <chao.peng@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/acpi/device_pm.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/acpi/device_pm.c b/drivers/acpi/device_pm.c
index a0bd9b4..b5ccc81 100644
--- a/drivers/acpi/device_pm.c
+++ b/drivers/acpi/device_pm.c
@@ -115,7 +115,7 @@ const char *acpi_power_state_string(int state)
 	case ACPI_STATE_D3_HOT:
 		return "D3hot";
 	case ACPI_STATE_D3_COLD:
-		return "D3";
+		return "D3cold";
 	default:
 		return "(unknown)";
 	}
